<TITLE> DSE plays good in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com) - Dhaka stocks played upbeat in midday trade Monday triggered by a rush in the buying of Square Pharmaceuticals shares after the company posted dividend results. Indices fell sharply at the beginning of the day on reports of the arrest of former prime minister and AL president Sheikh Hasina. Security forces arrested Hasina and took her away from her Dhanmondi home at 7:31 am Monday. "The market came back on the Square Pharma dividend announcement," said Salahuddin Ahmed Khan, chief executive of Dhaka Stock Exchange. The market recovered a bit but fell again and continued until it regained pace, spurred by the dividend results of Square Pharma, which reached the DSE at 11 am. Square announced a 50 percent cash dividend and 50 percent stocks for the year that ended March 31, 2007. The DGEN or general index rallied 18.49 points or 0.82 percent to reach 2247.88 at 11.57 am. The DSI or all-share price index added 11.41 points or 0.62 percent to 1841.64. Losers, however, beat gainers 72 to 63. A total of 19 issues held steady. Turnover reached Tk 976.27 million. On Sunday, total turnover was Tk 1.65 billion. Square Pharmaceuticals, Southeast Bank, BRAC Bank, Prime Bank and Shahjalal Bank topped the turnover board at 11.39 am. Square Pharma went up to Tk 4163.25 from Sunday's close of Tk 3788.25. It scored Tk 105.24 million in turnover. Southeast Bank advanced to Tk 505.5 from Tk 494.75 on buying pressure. BRAC Bank, however, dropped slightly to Tk 790 from Tk 790.25. Prime Bank gained Tk 780 from Tk 757. Shahjalal Bank upped Tk 255.25 from Tk 247. Of the remaining issues on the turnover table, Heidelberg Cement, Summit Power, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh and DESCO traded lower. But UCBL advanced. bdne
